{"type":"message","id":"4fa394df","parentId":"2718bef8","timestamp":"2026-03-12T16:27:52.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cask requires macOS Sequoia but the machine is running macOS 13 (Ventura). Let me check the exact version and see if there's an alternative.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The Homebrew cask failed — it requires **macOS Sequoia (15+)** and your machine is running **macOS 13 (Ventura)**. \n\nUnfortunately, the OpenClaw macOS companion app won't install on this OS version. Here are your options:\n\n1. **Upgrade macOS** — If your hardware supports it, upgrading to macOS Sequoia would let you install the app via `brew install --cask openclaw`.\n\n2. **Keep using the CLI** — You already have the OpenClaw Gateway running via the CLI (`openclaw` command), which is how you're talking to me right now. The macOS app is mainly a convenience layer that adds:\n   - Menu bar icon & native notifications\n   - TCC permission management (camera, screen recording, mic)\n   - Canvas UI overlay\n   - `system.run` exec approvals UI\n\n3. **Check for an older compatible release** — though the cask explicitly gates on Sequoia, so older builds likely have the same requirement.\n\nWant me to check your macOS version and hardware to see if a Sequoia upgrade is possible?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":306,"cacheRead":57554,"cacheWrite":145,"totalTokens":58006,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0076500000000000005,"cacheRead":0.028776999999999997,"cacheWrite":0.00090625,"total":0.037338249999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773332859515}}
